  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 85339989043ca1a409c4e5230098884b, type: 3}
  m_Name: Brief History of Magic
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  bookTitle: Brief History of Magic
  coverImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: c9cd8d3b2e0b6694383ed2ddcefab711, type: 3}
  worldIcon: {fileID: 21300000, guid: c9cd8d3b2e0b6694383ed2ddcefab711, type: 3}
  pageContent: "\"...The first age of magic began not with spells, but with observing
    the stars. Ancient mages realized that energy flows through the world like invisible
    rivers. To channel this power, the first staffs were carved from the wood of
    the World Tree. The most dangerous spell of that era \u2014 the Ether Rip \u2014
    is still considered forbidden today, as it is capable of erasing the boundaries
    between reality and the world of dreams with just one wave of a hand...\""
